metadata.name: Whiteish patient
metadata.description:
The waiting room was empty and no sound could be heard,
Whiteish felt like he was alone in the entire world.

Than a sexy nurse approached him with a mocking smile
and told him arrogantly “Sit down and wait awhile”.

After which she went for a nurses lunch break,
without giving a shit for his headache.

The head hurt so bad that he started to hallucinate a bit
seeing doctors waiting in the room as patients and similar shit.

Strange figures suddenly sat around in the room,
With sadness in their stand and faces made of gloom.

The temperature got him high like amphetamine,
and suddenly he sees things the way he has never seen.

The provocatively uniformed nurse which was more than hot,
made him realise the following cognitive thought:

“Here she is a health care worker and I am a dog with albinism,
but as soon as I get out of this building
we will both become actors in the society of consumerism.”

“This fewer must have made me pathetic and cynic”,
he concluded and merged in the environment of clinic
in the role of a patient in every sense,
among imaginary people unable to pay private treatment expense.
